        "content": "<p>TartanLlama opened <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/12241\">PR #12241</a> from <code>TartanLlama:sy/yield-to-sync</code> to <code>bytecodealliance:main</code>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/WebAssembly/component-model/commit/7479890cb506d0f8f687595a4d41361ff8a2a194\">https://github.com/WebAssembly/component-model/commit/7479890cb506d0f8f687595a4d41361ff8a2a194</a> made blocking calls in sync contexts a trap condition. However, <code>thread.yield-to</code> is allowed in these contexts. <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/commit/8992b99bf44eb8b91820586b85f58512fd4d7c1c\">https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/commit/8992b99bf44eb8b91820586b85f58512fd4d7c1c</a> implemented these changes, but also disallowed <code>thread.yield-to</code>. This patch relaxes the relevant trap check.</p>\n<p>Testing added here: <a href=\"https://github.com/WebAssembly/component-model/pull/590\">https://github.com/WebAssembly/component-model/pull/590</a></p>\n</blockquote>",
